structured.description: An immediately invoked function expression (IIFE) named `fn`. The IIFE is a self-contained block of code that executes immediately when it's defined, without being called explicitly. It uses the `console.log` method from the browser's JavaScript console to output the string representation of the integer value 0.

items.description: Defines a constant function that logs the value `0` to the console when invoked, without any arguments or return values. It does not change state or depend on external inputs, making it a pure function with a single, predictable output.
items.name: fn
